<div class="banner">
  <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center mb-3">
    <div class="col-9 col-md-6">
        <h1>Your trip to the stars starts now</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-9 col-md-6">
      <form novalidate="novalidate" class="simple_form search" action="/" accept-charset="UTF-8" method="get"><input name="utf8" type="hidden" value="&#x2713;" />
        <div class="search-form-control form-group">
          <input class="form-control string required" type="text" name="search[query]" id="search_query" placeholder="Galaxy, age, composition... " />
          <button name="button" type="submit" class="btn btn-flat">
            <i class="fas fa-search"></i> Search
          </button>
        </div>
      </form>      
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <h2>How does rent a star works ? </h2>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card-category">
        <%= image_tag 'planet-star.png' %>
        <h3>The star you are looking for</h3>
        <p>
          Whether you’re looking for a star for the weekend or an entire constellation of stars for the whole family, a warm welcome awaits. Behind every trip with us is a real martian who can give you the details you need to check in and feel at home.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-category">
        <%= image_tag 'footplanet.png' %>
        <h3>A unique experience</h3>
        <p>
          Rent a Star Experiences are not your typical Star Tour. Whether you’re on a spatial trip, exploring your own galaxy, or staying on your home star, learn something new from an expert host. Choose from Dejarik lessons, pod racing – even yoga with goats.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-category">
        <%= image_tag 'keyhole.png' %>
        <h3>An easy process</h3>
        <p>
          Use filters to find exactly what you are looking for like price range or a pool – to get exactly what you want.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

